class KadasAnnotationProjectIntegration : QObject
{
%Docstring(signature="appended")
Wires the save-time shadow mechanism into the active
:py:class:`QgsProject`.

On construction this object connects to \c
:py:class:`QgsProject`.readProject so any Kadas-shadow items left over
in a project file (e.g. one saved by an older Kadas session that wasn't
cleaned up) are stripped after load, leaving the in-memory layer
pristine.

The save half of the lifecycle is driven explicitly by callers: \c
KadasApplication.projectSave() is expected to call \c
:py:func:`~prepareForSave` immediately before \c
:py:func:`QgsProject.write()` and \c :py:func:`~stripAfterSave`
immediately after, so the on-disk project contains the QGIS-compat
shadows but the running session does not.

Single instance owned by \c KadasApplication.
%End

%TypeHeaderCode
#include "kadas/gui/annotationitems/kadasannotationprojectintegration.h"
%End
  public:
    explicit KadasAnnotationProjectIntegration( QObject *parent = 0 );

    void prepareForSave();
%Docstring
calls \c KadasAnnotationLayerHelpers.prepareLayerForSave on each.
%End

    void stripAfterSave();
%Docstring
calls \c KadasAnnotationLayerHelpers.stripShadowsFromLayer on each.
%End

};

